The paper focuses on controllable image-to-image translation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method uses a Generative Adversarial Network (GAN), which is a popular deep learning technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of object keypoints and human skeletons, which are related to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM). Overall, the paper's main focus on image-to-image translation and the use of GANs suggests that cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.GR, and cs.MM.
